    "description": "SCSsim is a tool designed for emulating single-cell genome sequencing data. It consists of three modules: 1) \u201csimuVars\u201d module aims to generate single cell genome from a given reference sequence by inserting user-defined genomic variations into genomic loci; 2) \u201clearnProfile\u201d component is developed to infer sequencing platform dependent profiles from real data; 3) \u201cgenReads\u201d utility is provided to mimic single-cell genome amplification and read generation procedures based on the results of \u201csimuVars\u201d and \u201clearnProfile\u201d.",
